tasks.description:
When a user says 'create new instrument' or 'create commodity' without providing all required fields, the bot should respond with a guided prompt asking for the missing information, instead of falling through to the list handler.

Update `src/gateway/internal/bot/executor.go`:

1. **Add intent detection BEFORE keyword handlers** — check if the message contains a CREATE/UPDATE verb + entity noun without full parameters:
   ```go
   // Detect incomplete create commands and guide the user
   if containsAny(lower, "create", "new", "add") {
       if containsAny(lower, "instrument") && !reCreateInstrument.MatchString(message) {
           return ChatResponse{
               Reply: "To create a new instrument, please provide:\n\n" +
                   "`create instrument <ID> <commodity> <month> <year> contract <size> tick <tick_size>`\n\n" +
                   "Example: `create instrument RIC-2027M07 rice jul 2027 contract 5000 tick 0.01`\n\n" +
                   "Available commodities: wheat, corn, soybeans, barley, cashmere, cattle\n" +
                   "Or type `list commodities` to see all.",
           }
       }
       if containsAny(lower, "commodity") && !reCreateCommodity.MatchString(message) {
           return ChatResponse{
               Reply: "To create a new commodity, provide:\n\n" +
                   "`create commodity <id> <category> <unit>`\n\n" +
                   "Example: `create commodity rice grain kg`\n\n" +
                   "Categories: grain, oilseed, livestock, dairy, fiber",
           }
       }
       if containsAny(lower, "fee") {
           // Guide for fee schedule vs fee rule
           return ChatResponse{
               Reply: "Fee management commands:\n\n" +
                   "`create fee schedule <name> <year>` — create new fee schedule\n" +
                   "`add fee rule <type> <tier> <rate_bps>` — add fee rule\n" +
                   "`set tier <tier> for <participant>` — set participant tier\n\n" +
                   "Example: `add fee rule trading farmer 10bps`",
           }
       }
       if containsAny(lower, "ticket", "bug", "issue") {
           return ChatResponse{
               Reply: "To create a ticket, describe the issue:\n\n" +
                   "`report a bug: <description>`\n" +
                   "`create ticket: <title> - <description>`\n\n" +
                   "Example: `report a bug: the margin page loads slowly`",
           }
       }
       if containsAny(lower, "receipt") {
           return ChatResponse{
               Reply: "To issue a warehouse receipt:\n\n" +
                   "`issue receipt <holder_id> <commodity> <quantity>`\n\n" +
                   "Example: `issue receipt farmer1 wheat 5000`",
           }
       }
       if containsAny(lower, "facility", "warehouse") {
           return ChatResponse{
               Reply: "To register a warehouse facility:\n\n" +
                   "`register facility <name>`\n\n" +
                   "Example: `register facility UB Grain Storage`",
           }
       }
   }
   ```

2. **Add intent disambiguation for ambiguous verbs** — when user says just 'instrument' or 'margin' without a verb:
   ```go
   // If message is just a noun without verb, ask what they want to do
   if isJustNoun(lower) {
       return ChatResponse{
           Reply: fmt.Sprintf("What would you like to do with %s?\n\n" +
               "• `show %s` — view current data\n" +
               "• `create %s` — create new\n" +
               "• Type `help` for all commands", noun, noun, noun),
       }
   }
   ```

3. **Improve the 'show'/'view' prefix handling** — currently 'show instruments' and 'create instrument' both match `containsAny(lower, "instrument")`. Add explicit show/list prefix detection:
   ```go
   // Explicit show/list/view commands → always list data
   if strings.HasPrefix(lower, "show ") || strings.HasPrefix(lower, "list ") || strings.HasPrefix(lower, "view ") {
       // ... route to list handlers
   }
   ```

4. **Move the keyword handlers (`containsAny`) to ONLY fire for show/list/query intent**, not for create/update:
   - `containsAny(lower, "instrument")` should NOT fire when the message also contains "create" or "new"
   - Add guard: `if !containsAny(lower, "create", "new", "add", "update", "set", "register") { ... list handler ... }`

5. **Add friendly error messages** instead of raw JSON dumps:
   - When API returns error, show: "❌ Could not create [entity]. Error: [friendly message]. Try: [example command]"
   - When API returns success, show: "✅ [Entity] '[name]' created successfully." (not raw JSON)

Acceptance:
- 'create new instrument' → asks for parameters (not lists instruments)
- 'create commodity' → asks for id/category/unit
- 'create commodity rice grain kg' → creates (existing behavior preserved)
- 'show instruments' → lists (existing behavior preserved)
- 'instrument' (just noun) → asks what they want to do
- All existing executor tests still pass
